OL,6,FMeanwhile in Scotland, the scheduling
OL,7,Fof the local soap River City has become
OL,8,Fa little erratic. It was off air last
OL,9,Fsummer and is now off the air again
OL,10,Funtil May. For its first 18 years it
OL,11,Fnever took a break.
OL,13,FWhy is this a problem?
OL,15,FFor a soap or a continuing drama,
OL,16,Fregularity is vital. The viewer needs
OL,17,Fto know it is there at a certain time.
OL,18,FOtherwise the relationship goes. When
OL,19,Fthe relationship goes and the ratings
OL,20,Ffall, a programme's future can
OL,21,Finevitably fall into question.
