OL,6,FThere is s strategic argument to
OL,7,Fexplore here though.
OL,9,FDoes the BBC really need to have soaps
OL,10,Fand continuing dramas? Should it focus
OL,11,Fits resources on one-offs, short-run
OL,12,Fdramas and big hitters with, say,
OL,13,Fannual runs of 8, 10 or 13 episodes?
OL,15,FThe respected writer Russell T. Davies
OL,16,Frecently suggested the number of
OL,17,Fepisodes of EastEnders should be scaled
OL,18,Fback. Certainly it could open up slots
OL,19,Fin the schedule and you might wonder if
OL,20,Fit might be easier for those with busy
OL,21,Flives to follow soaps again if there
OL,22,Fwere fewer episodes.
OL,3,CBBC soaps and continuing dramas:
OL,4,Cerratic scheduling and short-runs
